Two stars for the food: usually fine and as you would expect; a few times they’ve done something like giving us a sandwich in a you pick two that is mostly bread and little else, but that’s rare. We eat here frequently - they have a lot of nutritious salads and I like the creamy chicken and wild rice soup. Their oatmeal is also fantastic.  Minus two for service and one for the inconvenience their poor service causes: we always do a mobile order and they a l w a y s forget something on the order. Always. They’ve forgotten everything from cream cheese with a bagel to an entire sandwich. They also frequently mix their orders up. Especially soup. I’m usually not in a position to turn around and go back so refunds aren’t helpful. I’m not sure what the deal is - you can see they physically ticked off everything on the receipt. If you get take-out here you must unpack the entire bag, check that you have the number and type of items you ordered AND also check that the items are the correct ones. I usually don’t go at peak times so there’s no line or anything. If I find something missing I just go up to the prep area. Yes, they have attitudes, but most of the people that work there are just kids.
